# Slide authoring

Follow section order from `@docs/PRD.md`: title → overview → theory → best practices → practical → resources → Q&A/close.

## Density and structure

- Prefer **one idea per slide**
- Use two-column layouts for comparisons (e.g. rules vs skills)
- Implement **must-cover** first; keep stretch content clearly optional or in a short appendix
- Do not rely on HTML comment speaker notes for core meaning

## Demo cue slides

Each cue slide must include:

1. Goal (one sentence)
2. What the attendee should observe
3. Expected outcome class (e.g. “draft test + human review”)
4. Link to relevant Cursor docs when applicable

Cues may illustrate patterns from a live project; they must remain understandable without private-repo access.

## Links

Every non-trivial tool or claim with an official source needs a URL on that slide **or** on Resources. Prefer Resources as the single link-update hub.

Required checklist (verify URLs still resolve; update if Cursor moves docs):

| Topic | URL |
| --- | --- |
| Cursor docs | https://cursor.com/docs |
| Agent overview | https://cursor.com/docs/agent/overview |
